  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Weekly meetings of Savings and Learning Groups of between 12 and 20 people as a vehicle for micro-savings-based food security and micro-enterprise, WASH education, health education, community development and long-term formation of participant-led community development institutions. Groups are single-gender settings to meet the needs of cultural norms in Bangladesh, but teach skills for healthy social interaction and values for good relationships. Groups are self-led and facilitated by FH Staff, with direct contact one half day per group per week.</narrative>
  </description>
